column1: DO NOT SHARE THIS SHEET. CHOOSE "Download as CSV"

column3: definition
column4: Loading of a user generated and placed impression pixel for the purpose of creating an attributing event from a marketing effort. By this definition, no automated renders from Branch (e.g. Journeys, Deepviews) are impressions, nor are views of content in the app.
column5: A user initiated action of tapping on a Branch link or html element directly in front of a Branch link
column6: A web to app auto redirect works by simulating the action of a user clicking a link, but without user interaction. Technically this is implemented using "open_app=true" in our web to app products. Currently, this only exists on Journeys (+ banners + Web SDK Deepviews).
column7: The loading of a visual element or webpage that includes a Branch-created CTA, powered by a Branch link. Today, this includes loading Journeys and Deepviews.
column8: An successfully triggered call to send an SMS (not necessarily receipt of the SMS)
column9: A mobile app launch that is not an install (ie not a first time app launch for that persona). An "open" ends when an app is backgrounded or closed.
column10: The first time an app launches for a given IDFA/AAID. (Excludes cases where the IDFA is reset with the app still installed.)
column11: When an app is deleted then re-installed on the same device (same device is defined as same IDFA/AAID).
column12: A website launch (ie first page view). A session is considered to end after 30 minutes of inactivity (ie not launching a page or triggering an event).
column13: A pageview is the loading of a single page for a given website which is triggered more specifically, by calling branch.init() or branch.track('pageview')
column14: A standard event where a customer is on a journey to pay money to a business. It excludes views, but includes adding to cart through to purchasing. [Uses Branch event tracking code or the Data Ingestion pipeline. Each event within it is a point in time action.]
column15: Custom event is a non-standard user tracked event. [Uses Branch event tracking code or the Data Ingestion pipeline. Each event within it is a point in time action.]
column16: A standard event involving content that may or may not be a product, but excludes events where a customer is on a journey to pay money to a business (adding to cart to purchasing). [Uses Branch event tracking code. Each event within it is a point in time action.]
column17: A standard event not involving content. [Uses Branch event tracking code. Each event within it is a point in time action.]
